  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards and recommendations for combating money laundering and terrorist financing.\n\n2. The United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime provides a framework for international cooperation against money laundering.\n\n3. The Basel Committee on Banking Supervision offers guidelines for banks to prevent money laundering.\n\n4. Many countries have their own national laws, such as:\n- The U.S. Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union's Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- United Kingdom's Proceeds of Crime Act\n\nThese laws typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nInternational cooperation and information sharing are key components of combating money laundering across borders.",
